race.comment: SIEBERT (6) progressive Capitalist gelding unbeaten in two runs this campaign. Gave them a galloping lesson when up in trip and grade defeating Crimson Wings over 1200m at Gosford. Can get over from the sticky draw and keep the momentum going. CAN'T TOUCH THIS (2) Flying Artie mare racing in career best form. Was a month between runs when fading late to finish third over 1200m at Gosford. Claim helps and she has options from the draw. Hard to hold out. NOVEMBER AIR (5) defeated inferior opposition first-up when she sat on the speed and pulled out plenty, scoring over 1300m at Canberra. Races best early in the prep and the claim will help her cause. MISS BUSSLINGER (1) talented mare set to peak from the low gate. Covered ground from the sticky draw when a plugging fifth over 1300m at Randwick in BM72 company. Look for her pouncing late with Stanley's 2kg claim.
